                "response": "\n  <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal\">We agree and\n  this is the reason why we developed WP3, which explores what other behavioral\n  conditions need to be in place for adoption. Maybe farmers and consumers need\n  to be informed about the novel product (for which preferences did not yet\n  exist, e.g., biofortified or low-glycemic index crops), before they can\n  develop and express preferences and demand for these products. WP3 enables\n  testing these behavioral conditions that go beyond the product profile. WP2\n  is strongly connected to WP1 and WP3 through feedback loops. WP1 provides the\n  building blocks of forward-looking market intelligence, while WP2 feeds back\n  information to WP1 on what kind of market intelligence to look for. WP3 looks\n  beyond the product profile and feeds back information to WP2 that is relevant\n  for product profile design. During the inception phase we will make sure that\n  the process and interactions across WP are laid out in more detail.</p>\n  ",
