                "response": "\n  <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal\">We agree and\n  have systematically considered gender and social inclusion (GESI) from the\n  design stage forward to most tackle GESI challenges in each Work Package\n  (WP). GESI issues related to intra-household and across-community access to\n  technologies, markets, and products will be addressed in all WPs, with work\n  plans refined in a context- sensitive manner during inception. WP1, for\n  example, focuses on collaborative data generation and sharing and emphasizes\n  gender- and socio-cultural group disaggregated data collection. These data\n  will form an evidence base for remaining research in WPs 2-5. As detailed in\n  the proposal, WPs 2, 3 and 4 also specifically target women and girls,\n  expecting and young mothers, and women’s groups as key beneficiaries</p>\n  ",
