                "response": "\n  <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;line-height:normal\">As detailed\n  in the WP methods sections of TAFSSA proposal, formal literature scoping\n  and/or systematic reviews are integral to WPs 1, 3, 4 and 5. We are indeed\n  aware that there is an extensive international literature on food\n  environments, prices, and diets. But while a handful of studies on these\n  topics have focused on one or more countries in South Asia, few take an\n  integrated regional, cultural, and political perspective as proposed by\n  TAFSSA. We anticipate TAFSSA’s to fill this gap through comparative research\n  that aims to advance the field through regional synthesis and coordination by\n  means of learning platforms that bring together existing but disparate\n  efforts.</p>\n  ",
